The paper discusses the research field of Automated Planning, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on the timeline-based approach to planning, which involves integrating causal and temporal reasoning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions the application of this approach in real-world scenarios, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-categories of cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a formal characterization of the timeline-based approach capable of dealing with temporal uncertainty, which could suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
